The '''Immigration Act, 1906''' (also written as the '''Immigration Act of 1906''', assented July 13, 1906) was an act passed by the government of Canada that made the country's immigration policy more restrictive. It was developed under the guidance of [[Frank Oliver (politician)|Frank Oliver]], minister of the interior from 1905 to 1911.<ref name=pier21-immigration-act-1906>{{cite web|url = https://www.pier21.ca/research/immigration-history/immigration-act-1906|title = Immigration Act, 1906|title = Immigration Act, 1906|accessdate = November 24, 2017|publisher = Canada Museum of Immigration at Pier21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://immigrationtous.net/140-immigration-act-canada-1906.html|title = IMMIGRATION ACT (CANADA) (1906)|accessdate = November 20, 2017|publisher = Immigration to North America}}</ref><ref name=frank-oliver>{{Cite journal|url = https://journals.library.ualberta.ca/pi/index.php/pi/article/download/1415/958|title = "A brake upon the wheel": Frank Oliver and the Creation of the Immigration Act of 1906|last = Hollihan|first = K. Tony|journal = Past Imperfect|pages = 93-112|volume = 1|year = 1992|accessdate = November 24, 2017}}</ref><ref name=canada-immigration-policy-1896-1910>{{cite journal|url = https://www.jstor.org/stable/138931|title = Canada's Immigration Policy, 1896-1910|journal = The Canadian Journal of Economics and Political Science|volume = 26|number = 4|date = November 1, 1960|accessdate = November 24, 2017}}</ref><ref name=pier21>{{cite web|url = https://www.pier21.ca/research/immigration-history/canadian-immigration-acts-and-legislation|title = Canadian Immigration Acts and Legislation|last = Van Dyk|first = Lindsay|accessdate = November 24, 2017|publisher = Canada Museum of Immigration at Pier21}}</ref><ref name=passagetocanada>{{cite web|url = http://passagestocanada.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Primer_discrimination-in-immigration-policy_final1.pdf|title = Historical Timeline: Changes to Canadaâ€™s Immigration Policies|acce